theorem closure_compl_eq_compl_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (Aᶜ) = (interior A)ᶜ := by
  -- Start from the relation `interior (Aᶜᶜ) = (closure (Aᶜ))ᶜ`.
  have h₁ : interior A = (closure (Aᶜ))ᶜ := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using
      (interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (X := X) (A := Aᶜ))
  -- Complement both sides to connect the closures.
  have h₂ : (interior A)ᶜ = closure (Aᶜ) := by
    simpa [Set.compl_compl] using congrArg Set.compl h₁
  simpa [Set.compl_compl] using h₂.symm

theorem closure_compl_eq_compl_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (Aᶜ) = (interior A)ᶜ := by
  classical
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hxCl
    -- Assume, for contradiction, that `x ∈ interior A`.
    by_cases hInt : x ∈ interior A
    · -- Obtain an open neighbourhood `U` of `x` contained in `A`.
      rcases (Set.mem_interior).1 hInt with ⟨U, hUopen, hUsub, hxU⟩
      -- Since `x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)`, the set `U` meets `Aᶜ`.
      have hNon : (U ∩ Aᶜ).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff).1 hxCl U hUopen hxU
      rcases hNon with ⟨y, hyU, hyAcomp⟩
      -- But `U ⊆ A`, so `y ∈ A`, a contradiction.
      have : (y : X) ∈ A := hUsub hyU
      have : False := hyAcomp this
      exact (False.elim this)
    · -- If `x ∉ interior A`, then `x ∈ (interior A)ᶜ`.
      simpa using hInt
  · intro hxCompl
    -- We show that every neighbourhood of `x` meets `Aᶜ`.
    have hxNotInt : x ∉ interior A := hxCompl
    have hClosure : ∀ U : Set X, IsOpen U → x ∈ U → (U ∩ Aᶜ).Nonempty := by
      intro U hUopen hxU
      -- If `U ⊆ A`, then `x ∈ interior A`, contradicting `hxNotInt`.
      by_cases hSubset : U ⊆ A
      · have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A :=
          (Set.mem_interior).2 ⟨U, hUopen, hSubset, hxU⟩
        exact (hxNotInt hxIntA).elim
      · -- Otherwise, pick a point of `U` that is not in `A`.
        push_neg at hSubset
        rcases hSubset with ⟨y, hyU, hyNotA⟩
        exact ⟨y, And.intro hyU hyNotA⟩
    -- Conclude that `x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)`.
    exact (mem_closure_iff).2 hClosure

theorem closure_interInterior_subset_closureInterior_and_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior A ∩ B) ⊆ closure (interior A) ∩ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  have hx₁ : x ∈ closure (interior A) := by
    -- `interior A ∩ B` is contained in `interior A`
    have h_subset : interior A ∩ B ⊆ interior A := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.1
    exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx
  have hx₂ : x ∈ closure B := by
    -- `interior A ∩ B` is contained in `B`
    have h_subset : interior A ∩ B ⊆ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact hy.2
    exact (closure_mono h_subset) hx
  exact And.intro hx₁ hx₂
